# Fix Firebase Initialization & Xcode Deployment

## Goal
1. Resolve the `[core/no-app]` error by initializing Firebase correctly in [main.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/main.dart).
2. Refactor [SocialService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/social_service.dart#6-122) to prevent premature access to Firestore.
3. Provide instructions for App Store submission via Xcode UI, as requested by the user.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [main.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/main.dart)
- Import `firebase_core`.
- Call `await Firebase.initializeApp()` in [main()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/main.dart#11-31).

### Services
#### [MODIFY] [social_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/social_service.dart)
- Change `_firestore` to a getter or initialize it lazily to ensure it is only accessed after Firebase is ready.

## Xcode Deployment Instructions
To push to the App Store using Xcode (as requested):
1. Open the workspace in Xcode (I have already opened it for you).
2. Select **Product > Archive** from the top menu.
3. Once the archive is complete, the **Organizer** window will open.
4. Click **Distribute App** and follow the prompts to upload to App Store Connect.

## Verification Plan
1. Run the app on the device.
2. Sign in with Google.
3. **Expectation**: Firebase initialization succeeds, and user data is synced to Firestore without errors.
